{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":600,"text":"I've always wanted to be a cyborg."},{"time":2280,"text":"One of my favorite shows as a kid\nwas \"The Six Million Dollar Man,\""},{"time":5480,"text":"and this is a little bit closer\nto the 240-dollar man or so, but --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":8680,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":10000,"text":"At any rate, I would normally\nfeel very self-conscious and geeky"},{"time":13440,"text":"wearing this around,"},{"time":14680,"text":"but a few days ago\nI saw one world-renowned statistician"},{"time":18040,"text":"swallowing swords on stage here,"},{"time":19640,"text":"so I figure it's OK amongst this group."},{"time":23280,"text":"But that's not what I want\nto talk about today."},{"time":25520,"text":"I want to talk about toys,\nand the power that I see inherent in them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":29440,"text":"When I was a kid,\nI attended Montessori school"},{"time":31640,"text":"up to sixth grade in Atlanta, Georgia."},{"time":34040,"text":"And at the time\nI didn't think much about it,"},{"time":36200,"text":"but then later, I realized that that was\nthe high point of my education."},{"time":39640,"text":"From that point on, everything else\nwas pretty much downhill."},{"time":42920,"text":"And it wasn't until later,\nas I started making games, that --"},{"time":45880,"text":"I really actually\nthink of them more as toys."},{"time":48040,"text":"People call me a game designer,"},{"time":49600,"text":"but I really think\nof these things more as toys."},{"time":51880,"text":"I started getting very interested\nin Maria Montessori and her methods,"},{"time":55260,"text":"and the way she went about things,"},{"time":56940,"text":"and the way she thought it\nvery valuable for kids"},{"time":59300,"text":"to discover things on their own"},{"time":60860,"text":"rather than being taught\nthese things overtly."},{"time":63060,"text":"And she would design these toys,\nwhere kids in playing with the toys"},{"time":66320,"text":"would come to understand\nthese deep principles"},{"time":68520,"text":"of life and nature through play."},{"time":70120,"text":"And since they discovered this,\nit stuck with them so much more,"},{"time":73160,"text":"and also they would experience\ntheir own failures."},{"time":75560,"text":"There was a failure-based aspect\nto learning there. It was very important."},{"time":79080,"text":"And so, the games that I do,"},{"time":80480,"text":"I think of really more\nas modern Montessori toys."},{"time":82840,"text":"And I really kind of want them\nto be presented in a way"},{"time":85460,"text":"to where kids can kind of explore\nand discover their own principles."},{"time":88680,"text":"So a few years ago,"}]},{"cues":[{"time":89869,"text":"I started getting very interested\nin the SETI program."},{"time":92460,"text":"And that's the way I work."},{"time":93781,"text":"I get interested in different subjects,\nI dive in, research them,"},{"time":96882,"text":"and then try to figure out\nhow to craft a toy around that,"},{"time":99663,"text":"so that other people can experience\nthe same sense of discovery"},{"time":102664,"text":"that I did as I was learning that subject."},{"time":104727,"text":"And it led me to astrobiology,"},{"time":106208,"text":"the study of possible life\nin the universe."},{"time":108289,"text":"And then Drake's equation,"},{"time":109610,"text":"looking at the probability\nof life arising on planets,"},{"time":112211,"text":"how long it might last,\nhow many planets are out there."},{"time":114852,"text":"And I started looking\nat how interesting Drake's equation was,"},{"time":117813,"text":"because it spanned\nall these different subjects --"},{"time":120214,"text":"physics, chemistry,\nsociology, economics, astronomy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":124160,"text":"And another thing that really\nimpressed me a long time ago"},{"time":126920,"text":"was \"Powers of Ten,\"\nCharles and Ray Eames' film."},{"time":129919,"text":"And I started putting those two together\nand wondering, could I build a toy"},{"time":133520,"text":"where kids would trip across\nall these interesting principles of life,"},{"time":136880,"text":"as it exists and as it might\ngo in the future."},{"time":139080,"text":"Things where you might trip across things"},{"time":141080,"text":"like the Copernican principle,\nthe Fermi paradox,"},{"time":143440,"text":"the anthropic principle,\nthe origin of life."}]},{"cues":[{"time":146000,"text":"And so I'm going to show you a toy today\nthat I've been working on,"},{"time":149200,"text":"that I think of more\nas kind of a philosophy toy."},{"time":152160,"text":"Playing this toy will bring up\nphilosophical questions in you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":155560,"text":"The game is \"Spore.\"\nI've been working on it for several years."},{"time":158640,"text":"It's getting pretty close to finished now."},{"time":160680,"text":"It occurs at all these different scales,\nfrom very small to very large."},{"time":164081,"text":"I'm going to pop in\nat the start of the game."},{"time":166242,"text":"And you actually start this game\nin a drop of water,"},{"time":168723,"text":"as a very, very small\nsingle-cell creature,"},{"time":170764,"text":"and right off the bat you basically\njust have to live, survive, reproduce."},{"time":174821,"text":"So here we are,\nat a very microscopic scale,"},{"time":177800,"text":"swimming around."},{"time":179280,"text":"And I actually realize\nthat cells don't have eyes,"},{"time":181680,"text":"but it helps to make it cute."}]},{"cues":[{"time":184000,"text":"The players are going to play\nthrough every generation of this species,"},{"time":187880,"text":"and as you play the game,"},{"time":189160,"text":"the creature is actually\ngrowing bit by bit."},{"time":191280,"text":"And as we start growing,"},{"time":192880,"text":"the camera will\nactually start zooming out,"},{"time":194960,"text":"and things that you see\nin the background there"},{"time":197200,"text":"will start slowly\npulling into the foreground,"},{"time":199400,"text":"showing you a little bit of what\nyou'll be interacting with as you grow."},{"time":202840,"text":"So as we eat, the camera\nstarts pulling out,"},{"time":205000,"text":"and then we start interacting\nwith larger and larger organisms."}]},{"cues":[{"time":208000,"text":"We actually play\nthrough many generations here,"},{"time":210240,"text":"at the cellular scale."},{"time":211480,"text":"I'm going to skip ahead here."},{"time":212920,"text":"At some point we get larger,"},{"time":214320,"text":"and we actually get\nto a macroevolution scale."},{"time":218102,"text":"Now, at this point\nwe're leaving the water,"},{"time":221000,"text":"and one thing that's kind of important\nabout this game is that, at every level,"},{"time":224760,"text":"the player is designing their creature,"},{"time":227040,"text":"and that's a fundamental aspect of this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":229000,"text":"Now, in the evolution game here,\nthe creature scale,"},{"time":232000,"text":"basically you have to eat,\nsurvive, and then reproduce."},{"time":234600,"text":"You know, very Darwinian."},{"time":236440,"text":"One thing we noticed with \"The Sims,\"\na game I did earlier,"},{"time":239440,"text":"is that players love making stuff."},{"time":241120,"text":"When they were able\nto make stuff in the game,"},{"time":243320,"text":"they had a lot of empathy\nin connection to it."},{"time":245561,"text":"Even if it wasn't as pretty"},{"time":247261,"text":"as a professional artist\nwould make for games,"},{"time":249976,"text":"it really stuck with them"},{"time":251217,"text":"and they really cared\nabout what would happen to it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":253698,"text":"At this point, we've left the water,\nand now with this little creature --"},{"time":257152,"text":"we could bring up\nthe volume a little bit --"},{"time":259246,"text":"and now we might try to eat."},{"time":261814,"text":"We might sneak up\non this little guy over here maybe,"},{"time":266080,"text":"and try and eat him."},{"time":268160,"text":"OK, well, we fight."}]},{"cues":[{"time":269400,"text":"(Creatures grunting)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":272760,"text":"OK, we got him."},{"time":275280,"text":"Now we get a meal."},{"time":278344,"text":"So really, at this part of the game,"},{"time":280120,"text":"what we're doing is we're\nrunning around and surviving,"},{"time":282760,"text":"and also getting to the next generation,"},{"time":284720,"text":"because we're going to play\nthrough every generation of this creature."},{"time":288040,"text":"We can mate, so I'm going to see"},{"time":289640,"text":"if one of these creatures\nwants to mate with me. Yeah."}]},{"cues":[{"time":296636,"text":"(Creatures grunting)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":298680,"text":"We didn't want to replay\nactual evolution with humans and all that,"},{"time":302520,"text":"because it's almost more interesting"},{"time":304280,"text":"to look at alternate\npossibilities in evolution."},{"time":306560,"text":"Evolution is usually presented\nas this one path that we took through,"},{"time":309840,"text":"but really it represents\nthis huge set of possibilities."},{"time":312520,"text":"Now, once we mate, we click on the egg."},{"time":314440,"text":"And this is where the game\nstarts getting interesting,"},{"time":317000,"text":"because one of the things\nwe really focused on here"},{"time":319440,"text":"was giving the players\nvery high-leverage tools,"},{"time":321720,"text":"so that for very little effort,\nthe player can make something very cool."},{"time":325320,"text":"And it involves a lot\nof intelligence on the tool side."}]},{"cues":[{"time":328000,"text":"But basically, this is the editor"},{"time":329600,"text":"where we're going to design\nthe next generation."},{"time":331902,"text":"So it has a little spine.\nI can move around, I can extend."},{"time":334960,"text":"I can also inflate or deflate it\nwith the mouse wheel,"},{"time":337520,"text":"so you sculpt it like clay."},{"time":338880,"text":"We have parts here\nthat I can put on or pull off."},{"time":341240,"text":"The idea is that the player\ncan basically design"},{"time":343520,"text":"anything they can think of in this editor,"},{"time":345560,"text":"and we'll basically bring it to life."},{"time":347400,"text":"So I might put some limbs\non the character here."},{"time":349680,"text":"I'll inflate them kind of large."},{"time":351280,"text":"And in this case\nI might decide I'm going to put --"},{"time":355920,"text":"I'll put mouths on the limbs."}]},{"cues":[{"time":360880,"text":"So pretty much players are encouraged\nto be very creative in the game."},{"time":365120,"text":"Here, I'll give it one eye in the middle,\nmaybe scale it up a bit. Point it down."},{"time":369440,"text":"And I'll also give it a few legs."},{"time":374120,"text":"So in some sense"},{"time":375360,"text":"we want this to feel like an amplifier\nfor the player's imagination,"},{"time":378800,"text":"so that with a very small number of clicks\na player can create something"},{"time":382560,"text":"that they didn't really think\nwas possible before."},{"time":384960,"text":"This is almost like designing\nsomething like Maya --"},{"time":387440,"text":"that an eight-year-old can use."},{"time":388960,"text":"But really the goal here was,"},{"time":390400,"text":"within about a minute,\nI wanted somebody to replicate"},{"time":392920,"text":"what typically takes a pictorial artist\nseveral weeks to create."},{"time":396200,"text":"OK, now I'll put some hands on it."},{"time":398160,"text":"OK, so here I've basically\nthrown together a little creature."},{"time":401080,"text":"Let me give it a little weapon\non the tail here, so it can fight."},{"time":404880,"text":"OK, so that's the complete model."},{"time":406520,"text":"Now we can actually\ngo to the painting phase."}]},{"cues":[{"time":408680,"text":"At this phase, the program\nhas some understanding"},{"time":411200,"text":"of the topology of this creature."},{"time":412840,"text":"It knows where the backbone is,\nwhere the spine, the limbs are,"},{"time":415900,"text":"how stripes should run,\nhow it should be shaded."},{"time":418180,"text":"And so we're procedurally\ngenerating the texture map,"},{"time":420700,"text":"something a texture artist\nwould take many days to work on."},{"time":423600,"text":"And then we can test it out,\nand see how it would move around."},{"time":426560,"text":"And so at this point the computer\nis procedurally animating this creature."},{"time":430080,"text":"It's looking at whatever I've designed.\nIt will actually bring it to life."},{"time":433600,"text":"And I can see how it might dance."}]},{"cues":[{"time":435200,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":436440,"text":"How it might show emotions,\nhow it might fight."},{"time":440640,"text":"So it's acting with its two mouths there."},{"time":442640,"text":"I can even have it pose for a photo."},{"time":444520,"text":"Snap a little photo of it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":446000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":448000,"text":"So then I bring this back into the game."},{"time":450040,"text":"It's born, and I play the next generation\nof my creature through evolution."},{"time":453600,"text":"Now again, the empathy\nthat the players have"},{"time":456080,"text":"when they create\nthe content is tremendous."},{"time":458120,"text":"When players create content in this game,\nit's automatically sent up to a server"},{"time":461920,"text":"and then redistributed\nto all the other players transparently."},{"time":464880,"text":"So in fact, as I'm interacting\nin this world with other creatures,"},{"time":468040,"text":"these creatures are transparently\ncoming from other players as they play."},{"time":471960,"text":"So the process of playing the game"},{"time":473640,"text":"is a process of building up\nthis huge database of content."},{"time":476520,"text":"And pretty much everything\nyou're going to see in this game,"},{"time":479400,"text":"there's an editor for\nthat the player can create,"},{"time":482080,"text":"up through civilization."},{"time":483703,"text":"This is my baby. When I eat,\nI'll actually start growing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":486420,"text":"This is the next generation.\nBut I'm going to skip ahead here."},{"time":489480,"text":"Normally what would happen is\nthese creatures would work their way up,"},{"time":492840,"text":"eventually become intelligent."},{"time":494320,"text":"I'd start dealing with tribes, cities\nand civilizations of them over time."},{"time":497840,"text":"I'm going to skip way ahead\nto the space phase."},{"time":500080,"text":"Eventually they would go out into space,"},{"time":502040,"text":"and start colonizing\nand exploring the universe."},{"time":505680,"text":"Now, really, in some sense,"},{"time":507382,"text":"I want the players to be building\nthis world in their imagination,"},{"time":510680,"text":"and then extracting it from them\nwith the least amount of pain."}]},{"cues":[{"time":513720,"text":"So that's kind of\nwhat these tools are about."},{"time":515880,"text":"How do we make the gameplay,"},{"time":518159,"text":"you know, basically\nthe player's imagination amplifier?"},{"time":521360,"text":"And how do we make\nthese tools, these editors,"},{"time":524090,"text":"something that are just as fun\nas the game itself?"},{"time":527120,"text":"So this is the planet\nthat we've been playing on"},{"time":529400,"text":"up to this point in the game."},{"time":531080,"text":"So far the entire game has been played\non the surface of this little world here."}]},{"cues":[{"time":534880,"text":"At this point we're actually\ndealing with a very little toy planet."},{"time":538080,"text":"Almost, again,\nlike the Montessori toy idea."},{"time":540200,"text":"What happens if you give\nsomebody a toy planet,"},{"time":542440,"text":"and let them play\nwith a lot of dynamics on it?"},{"time":544680,"text":"What could they discover?\nWhat might they learn on this?"},{"time":547360,"text":"This world was actually extracted\nfrom the player's imagination."},{"time":550400,"text":"So, this is the planet\nthat the player evolved on."},{"time":552800,"text":"Things like the buildings, the vehicles,\nthe architecture, civilizations"},{"time":556240,"text":"were all designed by the player\nup to this point."},{"time":558600,"text":"So here's a little city with some\nof our guys walking around in it."},{"time":561800,"text":"And most games put the player\nin the role of Luke Skywalker,"},{"time":564680,"text":"this protagonist\nplaying through this story."},{"time":566800,"text":"This is more about putting the player\nin the role of George Lucas."},{"time":569960,"text":"I want them, after they've\nplayed this game,"},{"time":572080,"text":"to have extracted an entire world\nthat they're now interacting with."}]},{"cues":[{"time":575320,"text":"As we pull down here,"},{"time":576560,"text":"we still have a whole set of creatures\nliving on the surface of the planet."},{"time":580120,"text":"All these different\ndynamics going on here."},{"time":582160,"text":"I can look over here, and this is\na little simplified food web"},{"time":585120,"text":"that's going on with the creatures."},{"time":586840,"text":"I can open this up and then scan\nwhat exists on the surface."}]},{"cues":[{"time":589720,"text":"You get some sense of the diversity\nof creatures that were brought in."},{"time":593100,"text":"Some of these were created by the player,"},{"time":595100,"text":"others by other players,\nautomatically sent over here."},{"time":597720,"text":"But there's a very simple\ncalculation of what's required,"},{"time":600460,"text":"how many plants are required\nfor the herbivores to live,"},{"time":603140,"text":"how many herbivores\nfor the carnivores to eat, etc.,"},{"time":605620,"text":"that you have to balance actively."},{"time":607300,"text":"Also with this phase,"},{"time":608540,"text":"we're getting more and more\nGod-like powers for the player,"},{"time":611340,"text":"and you can experiment\nwith this planet as a toy."},{"time":613680,"text":"So I can come in and I can do things,"},{"time":615480,"text":"and just treat this planet\nas a lump of clay."},{"time":617600,"text":"We have very simple\nweather systems, simple geology."},{"time":620081,"text":"For instance, I could open one of my tools\nhere and then carve out rivers."},{"time":624920,"text":"So this whole thing is kind of\nlike a big lump of clay, a sculpture."},{"time":628160,"text":"I can also play with the dynamics\nin this world over time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":630920,"text":"So one of the things I can do"},{"time":632360,"text":"is start pumping more CO2 gases\ninto the atmosphere,"},{"time":635760,"text":"and so that's what I'm doing here."},{"time":637440,"text":"There's actually\na little readout down there"},{"time":639560,"text":"of our planetary atmosphere,\npressure and temperature."},{"time":642880,"text":"So as I start pumping in more atmosphere,"},{"time":644880,"text":"we're going to start pushing up\nthe greenhouse gases here"},{"time":647600,"text":"and if you'll start noticing,"},{"time":649040,"text":"we start seeing\nthe ocean levels rise over time."},{"time":651880,"text":"And our cities\nare going to be at risk too,"},{"time":653960,"text":"because a lot of these are coastal cities."},{"time":656000,"text":"You can see the ocean levels\nare rising now"},{"time":658040,"text":"and as they encroach upon the cities,\nI'll start losing cities here."}]},{"cues":[{"time":661340,"text":"So basically, I want the players\nto be able to experiment and explore"},{"time":664620,"text":"a huge amount of failure space."},{"time":666180,"text":"So there goes one city."},{"time":668467,"text":"Now, over time, this is\ngoing to heat up the planet."},{"time":670920,"text":"So at first what we're going to see"},{"time":672640,"text":"is a global ocean rise\nhere on this little toy planet,"},{"time":675200,"text":"but then over time --\nI can speed it up --"},{"time":677241,"text":"we'll see the heat impact of that as well."}]},{"cues":[{"time":679362,"text":"Not only will it get hotter,"},{"time":681289,"text":"but at some point it's going to get so hot\nthe oceans will evaporate."},{"time":684630,"text":"They'll go up, and then they'll evaporate,\nand that'll be my planet."},{"time":687971,"text":"So basically, what we're getting here"},{"time":689772,"text":"is the sequel to \"An Inconvenient Truth,\"\nin about two minutes,"},{"time":692773,"text":"and that actually brings up\nan interesting point about games."},{"time":695934,"text":"Now here, our entire oceans\nare evaporating off the surface,"},{"time":700120,"text":"and as it keeps getting hotter,"},{"time":701680,"text":"at some point the entire planet\nis going to melt down. Here it goes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":705240,"text":"So we're not only\nsimulating biological dynamics --"},{"time":707680,"text":"food webs and all that --"},{"time":708920,"text":"but also geologic, you know,\non a very simple core scale."},{"time":711640,"text":"And what's interesting to me about games"},{"time":713569,"text":"is that I think we can take\na lot of long-term dynamics"},{"time":716200,"text":"and compress them\ninto very short-term experiences."},{"time":719240,"text":"Because it's so hard for people\nto think 50 or 100 years out,"},{"time":722160,"text":"but when you can give them a toy,"},{"time":723800,"text":"and they can experience these\nlong-term dynamics in just a few minutes,"},{"time":727160,"text":"I think it's an entirely\ndifferent point of view,"},{"time":729520,"text":"where we're actually using the game\nto remap our intuition."},{"time":732320,"text":"It's almost in the same way"},{"time":733680,"text":"that a telescope or microscope\nrecalibrates your eyesight;"},{"time":736440,"text":"I think computer simulations\ncan recalibrate your instinct"},{"time":739200,"text":"across vast scales of both space and time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":741224,"text":"So here's our little solar system,"},{"time":742880,"text":"as we pull away\nfrom our melted planet here."},{"time":745000,"text":"We actually have a couple\nof other planets in this solar system."},{"time":748080,"text":"Let's fly to another one."},{"time":749320,"text":"We're going to have this unlimited\nnumber of worlds you can explore here."},{"time":752800,"text":"As we move into the future,"},{"time":754160,"text":"and we start going out\ninto space and doing stuff,"},{"time":756560,"text":"we're drawing a lot\nfrom things like science fiction."},{"time":759080,"text":"And all my favorite science fiction movies"},{"time":761120,"text":"I want to play out here\nas different dynamics."}]},{"cues":[{"time":763320,"text":"This planet actually has some life on it."},{"time":765320,"text":"Here it is, some indigenous\nlife down here."},{"time":767360,"text":"One of the tools\nI can eventually earn for my UFO"},{"time":769720,"text":"is a monolith that I can drop down."}]},{"cues":[{"time":771440,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":773960,"text":"Now, as you can see,"},{"time":776000,"text":"these guys are actually\nstarting to go up and bow to it,"},{"time":779320,"text":"and over time, once they touch it,\nthey will become intelligent."},{"time":782360,"text":"So I can actually\npick a species on a planet"},{"time":784480,"text":"and then make them sentient."},{"time":785880,"text":"Now they've actually\ngone to tribal dynamics."},{"time":788040,"text":"And now, because\nI'm actually the one here,"},{"time":790080,"text":"I can get out of the UFO and walk up,"},{"time":791920,"text":"and they should be worshipping me\nat this point as a god."},{"time":795040,"text":"At first they're a little freaked out."},{"time":801536,"text":"OK, well maybe they're not worshipping me."}]},{"cues":[{"time":803560,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":804600,"text":"I think I'll leave\nbefore they get hostile."}]},{"cues":[{"time":807720,"text":"But we basically want\na diversity of activities"},{"time":809960,"text":"the players can play through this."},{"time":811640,"text":"I want to be able to play"},{"time":812920,"text":"\"The Day the Earth Stood Still,\"\n\"2001: A Space Odyssey,\""},{"time":815640,"text":"\"Star Trek,\" \"War Of the Worlds.\""},{"time":817280,"text":"Now, as we pull away from this world --"},{"time":819280,"text":"we're going to keep\npulling away from the star now."},{"time":821720,"text":"One of the things that always\nfrustrated me about astronomy"},{"time":824560,"text":"when I was a kid"},{"time":825800,"text":"is how it was always presented\nso two-dimensionally and so static."},{"time":828960,"text":"As we pull away from the star here,"},{"time":830680,"text":"we're actually going now\nout into interstellar space,"},{"time":833200,"text":"and we're getting a sense\nof the space around our home star."}]},{"cues":[{"time":836080,"text":"What I really wanted to do\nis to present this, basically,"},{"time":838800,"text":"as wonderfully 3D as it is actually is."},{"time":841120,"text":"And also show the dynamics,"},{"time":843120,"text":"and a lot of the interesting objects\nthat you might find, like, in the Hubble,"},{"time":846840,"text":"at pretty much realistic\nfrequencies and scales."},{"time":849120,"text":"So most people\nhave no idea of the difference"},{"time":851280,"text":"between an emission nebula\nand a planetary nebula."},{"time":853680,"text":"But these are the things"},{"time":854960,"text":"that we can put\nin this little galaxy here."},{"time":857040,"text":"So we're flying over here\nto what looks like a black hole."},{"time":859800,"text":"I want to basically have\nthe entire zoo of Hubble objects"},{"time":862520,"text":"that people can interact with\nand play with, again, as toys."}]},{"cues":[{"time":865400,"text":"So here's a little black hole"},{"time":866840,"text":"that we probably\ndon't want to get too close to."},{"time":870120,"text":"But we also have stars and things as well."},{"time":872160,"text":"If we pull all the way back,\nwe start seeing the entire galaxy here,"},{"time":875640,"text":"kind of slowly in motion."},{"time":877600,"text":"Typically, when people present galaxies,"},{"time":880840,"text":"it's always beautiful photos,\nbut they're always static."},{"time":883547,"text":"And when you bring it forward in time\nand start animating it,"},{"time":886460,"text":"it's amazing what a galaxy\nwould look like fast forwarded."}]},{"cues":[{"time":889278,"text":"This would be about\na million years a second,"},{"time":891459,"text":"because you have about\none supernova every century."},{"time":894080,"text":"And so you'd have\nthis wonderful sparkling thing,"},{"time":896440,"text":"with the disk slowly rotating,"},{"time":897920,"text":"and this is roughly\nwhat it would look like."},{"time":900040,"text":"Part of this is about bringing\nthe beauty of the natural world"},{"time":903060,"text":"to somebody in a very imaginative way,"},{"time":904940,"text":"so that they can start\ncalibrating their instinct"},{"time":907300,"text":"across these vast scales\nof space and time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":909380,"text":"Chris was wondering what kind of gods\nthe players would become."},{"time":913640,"text":"Because if you think about it,"},{"time":915120,"text":"you're going to have 15-year-olds,\n20-year-olds flying around this universe."},{"time":918740,"text":"They might be a nurturing god."},{"time":920220,"text":"They might be bootstrapping\nlife on planets,"},{"time":922340,"text":"trying to terraform\nand spread civilization."},{"time":924460,"text":"You might be a vengeful god, conquesting,"},{"time":926720,"text":"because you actually can do that,\nyou can attack other intelligent races."},{"time":930200,"text":"You might be a networking god,\nbuilding alliances,"},{"time":933246,"text":"or just curious, going around and wanting\nto explore as much as you possibly can."}]},{"cues":[{"time":937682,"text":"But basically, the reason\nwhy I make toys like this"},{"time":941451,"text":"is because I think\nif there's one difference"},{"time":943737,"text":"I could possibly make in the world,"},{"time":946480,"text":"that I would choose to make,"},{"time":947880,"text":"it's that I would like\nto somehow give people"},{"time":950040,"text":"just a little bit better calibration\non long-term thinking."},{"time":952880,"text":"Because I think most of the problems\nthat our world is facing right now"},{"time":956240,"text":"are the result of short-term thinking,"},{"time":958080,"text":"and the fact that it is so hard for us\nto think 50, 100, or 1,000 years out."},{"time":962280,"text":"And I think by giving kids toys like this\nand letting them replay dynamics,"},{"time":965960,"text":"very long-term dynamics\nover the short term,"},{"time":968080,"text":"and getting some sense\nof what we're doing now,"},{"time":970320,"text":"what it's going to be like in 100 years,"},{"time":972280,"text":"I think probably is the most effective\nthing I can be doing to help the world."},{"time":976280,"text":"And so that's why I think\nthat toys can change the world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":978971,"text":"Thank you."}]}]}